questions.question:
(a) Differentiate between basic, derived, and user-defined data types in C with examples. (b) Explain the concept of variable declaration vs definition with memory allocation. (c) What is the output of the following code? Explain the memory representation of each variable.

#include <stdio.h>
int x = 10; // Global variable
void fun() {
    static int y = 5;
    int z = 3;
    printf("x=%d, y=%d, z=%d\n", x, y, z);
    x++; y++; z++;
}
int main() {
    fun();
    fun();
    return 0;
}
